# Portfolio Website Structure

This portfolio website is built with Next.js and React Bootstrap, showcasing skills in programming, AI prompt engineering, and cybersecurity.

## Core Files

- [pages/index.tsx](mdc:pages/index.tsx) - Main landing page with all sections (Hero, About, Skills, Projects, Certificates)
- [pages/_app.tsx](mdc:pages/_app.tsx) - Next.js App component wrapper
- [pages/jurnal.tsx](mdc:pages/jurnal.tsx) - Bug hunting journal page

## Components

- [components/Layout.tsx](mdc:components/Layout.tsx) - Main layout wrapper with header and footer
- [components/Header.tsx](mdc:components/Header.tsx) - Navigation header component
- [components/Footer.tsx](mdc:components/Footer.tsx) - Footer component with contact information
- [components/CertificatePlaceholder.tsx](mdc:components/CertificatePlaceholder.tsx) - Placeholder for certificate images

## Styling

- [styles/globals.css](mdc:styles/globals.css) - Global styles for the entire application

## Configuration

- [next.config.js](mdc:next.config.js) - Next.js configuration
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration

## Assets

Public assets are stored in:
- `/public/images/` - Image files including certificates
- `/public/files/` - Documents like resume


